{"word":"εὐθηνέω","slug":"εὐθηνέω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>εὐθηνέω</b></el> <el>(εὐθηνέω,) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b>only in <a href='S:present tense'>pres.</a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>to thrive, flourish, prosper</i>, <a href='S:Latin'>Lat.</a> <el>florere, vigere</el>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Demosthenes'>Dem.</a></b>:—<a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:dative'>dat.</a> <i>to abound in</i> a thing, <b>Hhymn.</b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a> in same sense, <el>οἱ Λακεδαιμόνιοι εὐθηνήθησαν</el> <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>; <el>τὴν πόλιν εὐθενεῖσθαι</el> <b><a href='S:Demosthenes'>Dem.</a></b><p/></div><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:derived, derivation'>deriv.</a> uncertain\n"}]}